<br />
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">I have never seen the men kill, but they can sure stop!<br />
Lots of archery is the keyword. Use the mos to pull the bows and pavises, then stack them on countless companies for later use. precision targeting and elevated fire work well together. The mumak rider is really cheap , so thats why there is 4 copies in the deck.<br />
<br />
I am trying ou the new hobbit discard strategy for the free peeps side. Its seems to work very well.<br />
I magine this: <br />
<br />
At site 1 you play sudden fury, you then discard pippin with warmed up a bit and play him out again for the double move using knocked on the head. at site 3 you use warmed up a bit to ditch rosie cotton. lets also say sam lost a skirmish somewhere in there. Thats 3 tokens on sudden fury already. Imagine how many tokens will be on there by site 5. Imagine having 4 copies out. (By discarding a hobbit you lose the skirmish). By end game, frodo and sam should be able to win each skirmish they fight. Sam can also reach strength 17 in this deck. <br />
Some changes I might make: <br />
<br />
add one copy of home and hearth if you are worried about corruption (even though pippin and tolman can make an easterling deck dry)<br />
<br />
Add the self discarder merry from ttt set incase you have no other way to discard him.<br />
<br />
I hope you all think this is as good as I think it is </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
